HEADWORD: Quadrable
<hw>Quad"ra*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Quadrate</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Math.)</fld> <def>That may be sqyared,
or reduced to an equivalent square; -- said of a surface when the area
limited by a curve can be exactly found, and expressed in a finite
number of algebraic terms.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quadragenarious</ent>⟦br⟧
